{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":717,"text":"An evolutionary biologist\nat Purdue University"},{"time":4014,"text":"named William Muir studied chickens."},{"time":7520,"text":"He was interested in productivity --"},{"time":9249,"text":"I think it's something\nthat concerns all of us --"},{"time":11539,"text":"but it's easy to measure in chickens\nbecause you just count the eggs."},{"time":14827,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":16527,"text":"He wanted to know what could make\nhis chickens more productive,"},{"time":19944,"text":"so he devised a beautiful experiment."},{"time":22870,"text":"Chickens live in groups, so first of all,\nhe selected just an average flock,"},{"time":27328,"text":"and he let it alone for six generations."},{"time":30718,"text":"But then he created a second group"},{"time":32807,"text":"of the individually\nmost productive chickens --"},{"time":35315,"text":"you could call them superchickens --"},{"time":38270,"text":"and he put them together in a superflock,"},{"time":40377,"text":"and each generation, he selected\nonly the most productive for breeding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45415,"text":"After six generations had passed,"},{"time":47969,"text":"what did he find?"},{"time":49717,"text":"Well, the first group, the average group,\nwas doing just fine."},{"time":53548,"text":"They were all plump and fully feathered"},{"time":56074,"text":"and egg production\nhad increased dramatically."},{"time":58702,"text":"What about the second group?"},{"time":61419,"text":"Well, all but three were dead."},{"time":64253,"text":"They'd pecked the rest to death."},{"time":66413,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":67990,"text":"The individually productive chickens\nhad only achieved their success"},{"time":73501,"text":"by suppressing the productivity\nof the rest."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78830,"text":"Now, as I've gone around the world\ntalking about this and telling this story"},{"time":82525,"text":"in all sorts of organizations\nand companies,"},{"time":84777,"text":"people have seen\nthe relevance almost instantly,"},{"time":87353,"text":"and they come up and they say\nthings to me like,"},{"time":89659,"text":"\"That superflock, that's my company.\""},{"time":92750,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":94715,"text":"Or, \"That's my country.\""},{"time":98226,"text":"Or, \"That's my life.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":100798,"text":"All my life I've been told that the way\nwe have to get ahead is to compete:"},{"time":104722,"text":"get into the right school,\nget into the right job, get to the top,"},{"time":108754,"text":"and I've really never found it\nvery inspiring."},{"time":112492,"text":"I've started and run businesses\nbecause invention is a joy,"},{"time":117275,"text":"and because working alongside\nbrilliant, creative people"},{"time":120595,"text":"is its own reward."},{"time":122755,"text":"And I've never really felt very motivated\nby pecking orders or by superchickens"},{"time":128397,"text":"or by superstars."},{"time":131276,"text":"But for the past 50 years,"},{"time":133220,"text":"we've run most organizations\nand some societies"},{"time":137452,"text":"along the superchicken model."},{"time":139960,"text":"We've thought that success is achieved\nby picking the superstars,"},{"time":143582,"text":"the brightest men,\nor occasionally women, in the room,"},{"time":147731,"text":"and giving them all the resources\nand all the power."},{"time":151430,"text":"And the result has been just the same\nas in William Muir's experiment:"},{"time":155493,"text":"aggression, dysfunction and waste."},{"time":160462,"text":"If the only way the most productive\ncan be successful"},{"time":164572,"text":"is by suppressing\nthe productivity of the rest,"},{"time":167753,"text":"then we badly need to find\na better way to work"},{"time":171236,"text":"and a richer way to live."},{"time":174510,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":178921,"text":"So what is it that makes some groups"},{"time":182915,"text":"obviously more successful\nand more productive than others?"},{"time":186700,"text":"Well, that's the question\na team at MIT took to research."},{"time":189974,"text":"They brought in hundreds of volunteers,"},{"time":192400,"text":"they put them into groups, and they\ngave them very hard problems to solve."},{"time":195894,"text":"And what happened was exactly\nwhat you'd expect,"},{"time":198625,"text":"that some groups were very much\nmore successful than others,"},{"time":201931,"text":"but what was really interesting\nwas that the high-achieving groups"},{"time":205461,"text":"were not those where they had\none or two people"},{"time":208108,"text":"with spectacularly high I.Q."},{"time":211149,"text":"Nor were the most successful groups\nthe ones that had the highest"},{"time":214748,"text":"aggregate I.Q."},{"time":217117,"text":"Instead, they had three characteristics,\nthe really successful teams."},{"time":222991,"text":"First of all, they showed high degrees\nof social sensitivity to each other."},{"time":228633,"text":"This is measured by something called\nthe Reading the Mind in the Eyes Test."},{"time":232232,"text":"It's broadly considered\na test for empathy,"},{"time":234717,"text":"and the groups that scored highly on this"},{"time":236914,"text":"did better."},{"time":238864,"text":"Secondly, the successful groups\ngave roughly equal time to each other,"},{"time":243972,"text":"so that no one voice dominated,"},{"time":246317,"text":"but neither were there any passengers."},{"time":249103,"text":"And thirdly, the more successful groups"},{"time":251820,"text":"had more women in them."},{"time":254165,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":256162,"text":"Now, was this because women\ntypically score more highly on"},{"time":260437,"text":"the Reading the Mind in the Eyes Test,"},{"time":262310,"text":"so you're getting a doubling down\non the empathy quotient?"},{"time":265037,"text":"Or was it because they brought\na more diverse perspective?"},{"time":267795,"text":"We don't really know, but the striking\nthing about this experiment"},{"time":271951,"text":"is that it showed what we know, which is\nsome groups do better than others,"},{"time":276380,"text":"but what's key to that"},{"time":278731,"text":"is their social connectedness\nto each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283543,"text":"So how does this play out\nin the real world?"},{"time":286375,"text":"Well, it means that what happens\nbetween people really counts,"},{"time":291716,"text":"because in groups that are highly\nattuned and sensitive to each other,"},{"time":295524,"text":"ideas can flow and grow."},{"time":298780,"text":"People don't get stuck.\nThey don't waste energy down dead ends."}]},{"cues":[{"time":302768,"text":"An example: Arup is one of the world's\nmost successful engineering firms,"},{"time":307482,"text":"and it was commissioned to build\nthe equestrian center"},{"time":310134,"text":"for the Beijing Olympics."},{"time":312000,"text":"Now, this building had to receive"},{"time":313826,"text":"two and a half thousand\nreally highly strung thoroughbred horses"},{"time":319120,"text":"that were coming off long-haul flights,"},{"time":321209,"text":"highly jet-lagged,\nnot feeling their finest."},{"time":324692,"text":"And the problem\nthe engineer confronted was,"},{"time":328104,"text":"what quantity of waste to cater for?"},{"time":332540,"text":"Now, you don't get taught this\nin engineering school -- (Laughter) --"},{"time":337184,"text":"and it's not really the kind of thing\nyou want to get wrong,"},{"time":340388,"text":"so he could have spent months\ntalking to vets, doing the research,"},{"time":343853,"text":"tweaking the spreadsheet."},{"time":345654,"text":"Instead, he asked for help"},{"time":348799,"text":"and he found someone who had designed\nthe Jockey Club in New York."},{"time":353285,"text":"The problem was solved in less than a day."},{"time":357404,"text":"Arup believes that\nthe culture of helpfulness"},{"time":360191,"text":"is central to their success."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363279,"text":"Now, helpfulness sounds really anemic,"},{"time":367400,"text":"but it's absolutely core\nto successful teams,"},{"time":371498,"text":"and it routinely outperforms\nindividual intelligence."},{"time":377117,"text":"Helpfulness means I don't\nhave to know everything,"},{"time":380322,"text":"I just have to work among people\nwho are good at getting and giving help."},{"time":385600,"text":"At SAP, they reckon that you can answer\nany question in 17 minutes."},{"time":392131,"text":"But there isn't a single\nhigh-tech company I've worked with"},{"time":395126,"text":"that imagines for a moment\nthat this is a technology issue,"},{"time":400571,"text":"because what drives helpfulness\nis people getting to know each other."},{"time":405771,"text":"Now that sounds so obvious, and we think\nit'll just happen normally,"},{"time":410782,"text":"but it doesn't."},{"time":412410,"text":"When I was running\nmy first software company,"},{"time":415704,"text":"I realized that we were getting stuck."},{"time":417738,"text":"There was a lot of friction,\nbut not much else,"},{"time":421523,"text":"and I gradually realized the brilliant,\ncreative people that I'd hired"},{"time":426399,"text":"didn't know each other."},{"time":428364,"text":"They were so focused\non their own individual work,"},{"time":432241,"text":"they didn't even know\nwho they were sitting next to,"},{"time":435970,"text":"and it was only when I insisted\nthat we stop working"},{"time":438541,"text":"and invest time in getting\nto know each other"},{"time":441125,"text":"that we achieved real momentum."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444813,"text":"Now, that was 20 years ago,\nand now I visit companies"},{"time":447409,"text":"that have banned coffee cups at desks"},{"time":450311,"text":"because they want people to hang out\naround the coffee machines"},{"time":454305,"text":"and talk to each other."},{"time":456139,"text":"The Swedes even have\na special term for this."},{"time":458647,"text":"They call it fika, which means\nmore than a coffee break."},{"time":462007,"text":"It means collective restoration."},{"time":465613,"text":"At Idexx, a company up in Maine,"},{"time":468724,"text":"they've created vegetable gardens\non campus so that people"},{"time":471516,"text":"from different parts of the business"},{"time":473768,"text":"can work together and get to know\nthe whole business that way."},{"time":478644,"text":"Have they all gone mad?"},{"time":480989,"text":"Quite the opposite -- they've figured out\nthat when the going gets tough,"},{"time":484542,"text":"and it always will get tough"},{"time":486585,"text":"if you're doing breakthrough work\nthat really matters,"},{"time":489301,"text":"what people need is social support,"},{"time":491972,"text":"and they need to know who to ask for help."},{"time":495199,"text":"Companies don't have ideas;\nonly people do."},{"time":499936,"text":"And what motivates people"},{"time":502536,"text":"are the bonds and loyalty and trust\nthey develop between each other."},{"time":507566,"text":"What matters is the mortar,"},{"time":511260,"text":"not just the bricks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514299,"text":"Now, when you put all of this together,"},{"time":516273,"text":"what you get is something\ncalled social capital."},{"time":519431,"text":"Social capital is the reliance\nand interdependency that builds trust."},{"time":524980,"text":"The term comes from sociologists\nwho were studying communities"},{"time":528471,"text":"that proved particularly resilient\nin times of stress."},{"time":533409,"text":"Social capital is what\ngives companies momentum,"},{"time":537960,"text":"and social capital\nis what makes companies robust."},{"time":544182,"text":"What does this mean in practical terms?"},{"time":546852,"text":"It means that time is everything,"},{"time":550759,"text":"because social capital\ncompounds with time."},{"time":555426,"text":"So teams that work together longer\nget better, because it takes time"},{"time":560534,"text":"to develop the trust you need\nfor real candor and openness."},{"time":566461,"text":"And time is what builds value."},{"time":570625,"text":"When Alex Pentland\nsuggested to one company"},{"time":572878,"text":"that they synchronize coffee breaks"},{"time":575594,"text":"so that people would have time\nto talk to each other,"},{"time":579495,"text":"profits went up 15 million dollars,"},{"time":582978,"text":"and employee satisfaction\nwent up 10 percent."},{"time":586832,"text":"Not a bad return on social capital,"},{"time":589933,"text":"which compounds even as you spend it."},{"time":593960,"text":"Now, this isn't about chumminess,\nand it's no charter for slackers,"},{"time":600022,"text":"because people who work this way\ntend to be kind of scratchy,"},{"time":604656,"text":"impatient, absolutely determined\nto think for themselves"},{"time":608690,"text":"because that's what their contribution is."},{"time":612680,"text":"Conflict is frequent\nbecause candor is safe."},{"time":618280,"text":"And that's how good ideas\nturn into great ideas,"},{"time":623471,"text":"because no idea is born fully formed."},{"time":626571,"text":"It emerges a little bit\nas a child is born,"},{"time":629900,"text":"kind of messy and confused,\nbut full of possibilities."},{"time":634489,"text":"And it's only through the generous\ncontribution, faith and challenge"},{"time":640610,"text":"that they achieve their potential."},{"time":643892,"text":"And that's what social capital supports."}]},{"cues":[{"time":649455,"text":"Now, we aren't really used\nto talking about this,"},{"time":652228,"text":"about talent, about creativity,\nin this way."},{"time":656198,"text":"We're used to talking about stars."},{"time":660262,"text":"So I started to wonder,\nwell, if we start working this way,"},{"time":664371,"text":"does that mean no more stars?"},{"time":667445,"text":"So I went and I sat in on the auditions"},{"time":669805,"text":"at the Royal Academy\nof Dramatic Art in London."},{"time":673661,"text":"And what I saw there really surprised me,"},{"time":676886,"text":"because the teachers weren't looking\nfor individual pyrotechnics."},{"time":681786,"text":"They were looking for what happened\nbetween the students,"},{"time":686476,"text":"because that's where the drama is."},{"time":690586,"text":"And when I talked\nto producers of hit albums,"},{"time":692875,"text":"they said, \"Oh sure, we have\nlots of superstars in music."},{"time":696103,"text":"It's just, they don't last very long."},{"time":699220,"text":"It's the outstanding collaborators\nwho enjoy the long careers,"},{"time":703220,"text":"because bringing out the best in others\nis how they found the best"},{"time":707432,"text":"in themselves.\""},{"time":709686,"text":"And when I went to visit companies\nthat are renowned"},{"time":712115,"text":"for their ingenuity and creativity,"},{"time":714182,"text":"I couldn't even see any superstars,"},{"time":717107,"text":"because everybody there really mattered."},{"time":721445,"text":"And when I reflected on my own career,"},{"time":724328,"text":"and the extraordinary people\nI've had the privilege to work with,"},{"time":728252,"text":"I realized how much more\nwe could give each other"},{"time":733796,"text":"if we just stopped trying\nto be superchickens."},{"time":739815,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":744970,"text":"Once you appreciate\ntruly how social work is,"},{"time":751346,"text":"a lot of things have to change."},{"time":754443,"text":"Management by talent contest\nhas routinely pitted"},{"time":758530,"text":"employees against each other."},{"time":760991,"text":"Now, rivalry has to be replaced\nby social capital."},{"time":766355,"text":"For decades, we've tried\nto motivate people with money,"},{"time":769480,"text":"even though we've got\na vast amount of research that shows"},{"time":772360,"text":"that money erodes social connectedness."},{"time":776851,"text":"Now, we need to let people\nmotivate each other."},{"time":782646,"text":"And for years, we've thought that leaders\nwere heroic soloists who were expected,"},{"time":787570,"text":"all by themselves,\nto solve complex problems."},{"time":790726,"text":"Now, we need to redefine leadership"},{"time":794278,"text":"as an activity in which\nconditions are created"},{"time":798342,"text":"in which everyone can do their most\ncourageous thinking together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804300,"text":"We know that this works."},{"time":808210,"text":"When the Montreal Protocol called\nfor the phasing out of CFCs,"},{"time":812505,"text":"the chlorofluorocarbons implicated\nin the hole in the ozone layer,"},{"time":816847,"text":"the risks were immense."},{"time":819332,"text":"CFCs were everywhere,"},{"time":822231,"text":"and nobody knew if a substitute\ncould be found."},{"time":825360,"text":"But one team that rose to the challenge\nadopted three key principles."},{"time":831289,"text":"The first was the head of engineering,\nFrank Maslen, said,"},{"time":834647,"text":"there will be no stars in this team."},{"time":837980,"text":"We need everybody."},{"time":840257,"text":"Everybody has a valid perspective."},{"time":843485,"text":"Second, we work to one standard only:"},{"time":847711,"text":"the best imaginable."},{"time":850590,"text":"And third, he told his boss,\nGeoff Tudhope,"},{"time":853632,"text":"that he had to butt out,"},{"time":855605,"text":"because he knew\nhow disruptive power can be."},{"time":858856,"text":"Now, this didn't mean Tudhope did nothing."},{"time":861689,"text":"He gave the team air cover,"},{"time":863430,"text":"and he listened to ensure\nthat they honored their principles."},{"time":868190,"text":"And it worked: Ahead of all the other\ncompanies tackling this hard problem,"},{"time":874260,"text":"this group cracked it first."},{"time":877738,"text":"And to date, the Montreal Protocol"},{"time":880339,"text":"is the most successful international\nenvironmental agreement"},{"time":886060,"text":"ever implemented."}]},{"cues":[{"time":889402,"text":"There was a lot at stake then,"},{"time":891940,"text":"and there's a lot at stake now,"},{"time":894679,"text":"and we won't solve our problems\nif we expect it to be solved"},{"time":899207,"text":"by a few supermen or superwomen."},{"time":901808,"text":"Now we need everybody,"},{"time":905314,"text":"because it is only when we accept\nthat everybody has value"},{"time":911540,"text":"that we will liberate the energy\nand imagination and momentum we need"},{"time":918586,"text":"to create the best beyond measure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":923360,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":926100,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}